    <!-- ============ Help dialog ============ -->
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Title">Help</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Ok">Got it</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Tasks.Title">Tasks</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Tasks.L1">Type in the bottom-right box and press Enter or click "Add" to create a task.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Tasks.L2">After typing, a panel with priority, due time and the "Reminder" toggle pops up above.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Tasks.L3">Pick a quick time (in 5 min … in 1 week) or use "Custom" down to the minute.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Tasks.L4">Click a task title to edit it; right-click a task to edit, clear the due date, complete or delete it.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Tasks.L5">Completed tasks move into the "Done" group automatically; unchecking restores them.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Tasks.L6">Drag tasks to reorder; long titles show only the beginning.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Tasks.L7">Right-click a task and choose "Pin / Unpin to top": a pinned top-level task keeps its whole family at the very top, regardless of the sort order.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Tasks.L8">When setting a due time or recurring reminder, just pick the date/time or enter a value and it applies instantly — no "Set" button needed; the "Clear" button on each undoes it anytime.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Subtasks.Title">Subtasks &amp; indenting</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Subtasks.L1">Select a task and press Tab to indent it into a subtask of the one above; Shift+Tab promotes it.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Subtasks.L2">The right-click menu also offers "Make subtask / Promote", up to 6 nesting levels.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Subtasks.L3">Indent levels are preserved through Markdown import/export (expressed as list nesting).</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Schedule.Title">Schedule / calendar</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Schedule.L1">Click the calendar button at the top-right of the content header to open or close the embedded schedule panel on the right.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Schedule.L2">Switch Day / Week / Month. Day and Week show a 0–24 hour axis on the left and place tasks by their due time — all 24 hours fit in one screen.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Schedule.L3">Click a task block in the calendar to view and edit it; drag the middle divider to resize the to-do list and the calendar.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Schedule.L4">With the calendar open, dragging the window edge resizes only the calendar — the to-do list keeps its width, and is resized only via the middle divider.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Voice.Title">Voice input</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Voice.L1">The microphone button next to the new-task box triggers Windows dictation (same as Win+H).</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Voice.L2">First use requires enabling voice typing under Settings → Time &amp; language → Speech.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Reminder.Title">Recurring reminders</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Reminder.L1">When creating a task, tick "Reminder" and set an interval (30 min by default).</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Reminder.L2">When it fires, a bottom-left notification appears and, if "Reminder sound" is on, a soft chime plays.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Reminder.L3">Reminders stop once a task is completed; right-click a task to toggle the switch anytime.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.IO.Title">Import / Export Markdown</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.IO.L1">"Import / Export" in the sidebar exports the current list to .md, or imports tasks from a .md file.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.IO.L2">The format is editor-friendly: groups use ## headings, each task line is - [ ] / - [x].</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.IO.L3">Subtask indents are written as two spaces per level and restored on import.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Dock.Title">Edge auto-hide</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Dock.L1">Drag the window to the top / left / right screen edge and it slides out and hides.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Dock.L2">Move the mouse to that screen edge to slide it back; it hides again once you move away.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Dock.L3">Drag the title bar again to undock and return to a normal window.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Group.Title">Groups</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Group.L1">The left sidebar is the group bar: click "All Tasks" to see everything, or a group name to switch.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Group.L2">"New Group" adds a custom group; drag groups to reorder them.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Group.L3">Right-click a group to change color / clear / delete it ("Done" cannot be deleted).</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Group.L4">Drag to resize the sidebar; "Collapse" folds it into a narrow icon rail, click again to expand.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Theme.Title">Themes &amp; settings</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Theme.L1">"Theme" switches built-in themes (incl. transparent, glass) or creates a custom theme.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Theme.L2">The top-right menu → "Settings" toggles run-at-startup, completion effect, completion sound and reminder sound.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Theme.L3">Click the sort button to the right of the title to choose a sort order.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Theme.L4">"Settings" lets you adjust the font, size and line spacing of task &amp; body text; changes apply instantly and are saved automatically.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Theme.L5">The theme picker is a separate, draggable, resizable window beside the app; ~90 palettes are grouped by style (Classic / Morandi / Macaron / Dunhuang / Mondrian / Memphis / Rococo / Matisse / Transparent), with a group bar to jump to any group.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Theme.L6">Right-click any theme to add or remove it from Favorites; the Favorites group sits first and can be drag-reordered; when empty it shows a right-click hint.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Theme.L7">Create / edit custom themes with the built-in HSV color picker; the whole UI (including the calendar) previews live while editing, and reverts to your previous theme if you close without saving. Right-click a custom theme to edit or delete it.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Window.Title">Window</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Window.L1">Top-right red / yellow / green: close to tray / minimize / maximize-restore.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Window.L2">Closing only hides to the system tray; double-click the tray icon to restore, right-click to quit.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Window.L3">The pin button to the left of the menu button keeps the window always on top.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Window.L4">When you choose "Show" from the tray while the window is hidden against a screen edge, it un-docks and re-centers automatically.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Update.Title">Auto-update / About</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Update.L1">On startup and periodically afterward, the app checks GitHub for a newer version and prompts you; one click downloads it and restarts into the new version (self-contained single file, no runtime install needed).</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Update.L2">You can choose "Skip this version" in the prompt, or turn off automatic update checks in Settings.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Update.L3">Top-right menu → "About" shows the current version and lets you manually check / download the latest build.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Contact.Title">Contact the developer</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="S.Help.Contact.L1">This project on GitHub: https://github.com/wangchao199703/MinimalTodoApp</sys:String>

